Tex Entry</a></li></ol></nav><h2 id=3D"introduction">1.
       Introduction<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extens=
ions/xep-0301.html#introduction"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the d=
ocument">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h2>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">This document defines a specification for real=
-time text transmitted in-band over an XMPP network.</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Real-time text is text transmitted instantly w=
hile it is being typed or created. The recipient can immediately read the s=
ender's text as it is written, without waiting. It allows text to be used a=
s conversationally as a telephone conversation, including in situations whe=
re speech is not practical (e.g., environments that must be quiet, environm=
ents too noisy to hear, restrictions on phone use, situations where speakin=
g is a privacy or security concern, and/or when participant(s) are deaf or =
hard of hearing). It is also used for transmission of live speech transcrip=
tion.</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Real-time text is found in various implementat=
ions:</p>
    <ul class=3D"" style=3D"">
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">The 'talk' command on UNIX systems since th=
e 1970's.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Session Initiation Protocol (SIP), utilizin=
g <span class=3D"ref" style=3D""><a href=3D"http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4=
103">RFC 4103</a></span>  [<a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.=
html#nt-idm45597907671488">1</a>] real-time text.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Instant messaging enhancements, including a=
 <span class=3D"ref" style=3D""><strong><a href=3D"http://tap.gallaudet.edu=
/rtt/">Gallaudet University</a></strong></span>
   [<a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#nt-idm455979076673=
44">2</a>] collaboration.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Next generation emergency services (<span c=
lass=3D"ref" style=3D""><a href=3D"http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6443">RFC =
6443</a></span>  [<a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#nt-i=
dm45597907661952">3</a>]).</li>
    </ul>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">For a visual animation of real-time text, see =
<span class=3D"ref" style=3D""><strong><a href=3D"http://www.realtimetext.o=
rg/">Real-Time Text Taskforce</a></strong></span>
   [<a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#nt-idm455979076577=
28">4</a>].</p>
    <h2 id=3D"requirements">2.
       Requirements<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extens=
ions/xep-0301.html#requirements"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the d=
ocument">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h2>
        <div class=3D"indent"><h3 id=3D"fluid_realtime_text">2.1 Fluid Real=
-Time Text<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-=
0301.html#fluid_realtime_text"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the doc=
ument">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h3>
    <ol start=3D"" class=3D"" style=3D"">
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Allow reliable transmission of real-time te=
xt with a low latency.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Support message editing in real-time, inclu=
ding text insertions and deletions.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Support transmission and reproduction of th=
e original intervals between key presses, to preserve look-and-feel of typi=
ng independently of transmission intervals.</li>
    </ol>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h3 id=3D"inband_transmission">2.2 In-Band Transm=
ission<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301=
.html#inband_transmission"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the documen=
t">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h3>
    <ol start=3D"" class=3D"" style=3D"">
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Be backwards compatible with XMPP clients t=
hat do not support real-time text.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Be compatible with <span class=3D"ref" styl=
e=3D""><a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0045.html">Multi-User Cha=
t (XEP-0045)</a></span>  [<a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.h=
tml#nt-idm45597907644352">5</a>] and simultaneous logins.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Minimize reliance on out-of-band transmissi=
on protocols, for simpler network traversal.</li>
    </ol>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h3 id=3D"flexible_and_interoperable">2.3 Flexibl=
e and Interoperable<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extens=
ions/xep-0301.html#flexible_and_interoperable"><abbr title=3D"Link to this =
point in the document">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h3>
    <ol start=3D"" class=3D"" style=3D"">
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Allow seamless integration of real-time tex=
t into instant messaging clients, with minimal user interface modifications=
.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Be able to function securely over intermitt=
ent and unreliable connections, including mobile phones.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Allow use within gateways to interoperate w=
ith other real-time text protocols, including <strong>RFC 4103</strong> and=
 <span class=3D"ref" style=3D""><strong><a href=3D"http://www.itu.int/rec/T=
-REC-T.140">ITU-T T.140</a></strong></span>
   [<a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#nt-idm455979076342=
72">6</a>].</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Be usable in an international setting.</li>
    </ol>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h3 id=3D"accessible">2.4 Accessible<a class=3D"a=
nchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#accessible"><=
abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the document">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h3>
    <ol start=3D"" class=3D"" style=3D"">
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Allow XMPP applications to be able to imple=
ment <span class=3D"ref" style=3D""><strong><a href=3D"http://www.itu.int/r=
ec/T-REC-F.703">ITU-T Rec. F.703</a></strong></span>
   [<a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#nt-idm455979076276=
48">7</a>] Total Conversation standard for simultaneous voice, video, and r=
eal-time text.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Be a candidate technology for use with next=
 generation emergency services (e.g., 9-1-1 and 1-1-2).</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Be suitable for transcription services and =
(when coupled with voice at user's choice) for TTY/text telephone alternati=
ves, relay services, and captioned telephone systems.</li>
    </ol>
    </div>
<h2 id=3D"glossary">3.
       Glossary<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions=
/xep-0301.html#glossary"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the document"=
>=C2=B6</abbr></a></h2>
    <div class=3D"indent"><dl><dt><strong>action element</strong></dt><dd>A=
n XML element that represents a single real-time message edit, such as text=
 insertion or deletion.</dd>
    <dt><strong>character</strong></dt><dd>A single Unicode code point. See=
 <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#unicode_character_cou=
nting">Unicode Character Counting</a>.</dd>
    <dt><strong>real-time</strong></dt><dd>A conversational latency of less=
 than 1 second, as defined by <span class=3D"ref" style=3D""><strong><a hre=
f=3D"http://www.itu.int/rec/T-REC-F.700">ITU-T Rec. F.700</a></strong></spa=
n>
   [<a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#nt-idm455979076188=
32">8</a>], section 2.1.2.1.</dd>
    <dt><strong>real-time text</strong></dt><dd>Text transmitted instantly =
while it is being typed or created, to allow recipient(s) to immediately re=
ad the sender's text as it is written, without waiting.</dd>
    <dt><strong>real-time message</strong></dt><dd>Recipient's real-time vi=
ew of the sender's message still being typed or created.</dd>
    <dt><strong>RTT</strong></dt><dd>Acronym for real-time text.</dd>
    <dt><strong>simultaneous login</strong></dt><dd>Multiple simultaneous s=
essions, on multiple clients, using the same login (Jabber Identifier).</dd=
></dl></div>
    <h2 id=3D"protocol">4.
       Protocol<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions=
/xep-0301.html#protocol"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the document"=
>=C2=B6</abbr></a></h2>
        <div class=3D"indent"><h3 id=3D"rtt_element">4.1 RTT Element<a clas=
s=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#rtt_ele=
ment"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the document">=C2=B6</abbr></a><=
/h3>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Real-time text is transmitted via an &lt;rtt/&=
gt; child element of a &lt;message/&gt; stanza. The &lt;rtt/&gt; element is=
 transmitted at regular intervals by the sender client while a message is b=
eing composed. This allows the recipient to see the latest message text fro=
m the sender, without waiting for the full message to be sent in a &lt;body=
/&gt; element.</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">This is a basic example of a <strong>real-time=
 message</strong> "Hello, my Juliet!=E2=80=9D transmitted in real-time whil=
e it is being typed, before a final message delivery in a &lt;body/&gt; ele=
ment (to remain <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#backwa=
rds_compatible">Backwards Compatible</a>):</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D""><strong>Example 1: Introductory Example</stron=
g></p>
    <figure class=3D"code"><figcaption></figcaption><pre class=3D"prettypri=
nt prettyprinted" style=3D""><span class=3D"tag">&lt;message</span><span cl=
ass=3D"pln"> </span><span class=3D"atn">to</span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</s=
pan><span class=3D"atv">'juliet@capulet.lit'</span><span class=3D"pln"> </s=
pan><span class=3D"atn">from</span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</span><span clas=
s=3D"atv">'romeo@montague.lit/orchard'</span><span class=3D"pln"> </span><s=
pan class=3D"atn">type</span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</span><span class=3D"a=
