my Juliet!</span><span class=3D"tag">&lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=3D"pln=
">
</span><span class=3D"tag">&lt;/message&gt;</span></pre></figure>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">The &lt;rtt/&gt; element contains one or more =
child elements that represent <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-03=
01.html#realtime_text_actions">Real-Time Text Actions</a> such as text bein=
g appended, inserted, or deleted. Example 1 illustrates only the &lt;t/&gt;=
 <strong>action element</strong>, which appends text to the end of a messag=
e.</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Transmission of the &lt;rtt/&gt; element occur=
s at a regular <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#transmi=
ssion_interval">Transmission Interval</a> whenever the sender is actively c=
omposing a message. If there are no changes to the message since the last t=
ransmission, no transmission occurs.</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">There MUST NOT be more than one &lt;rtt/&gt; e=
lement per &lt;message/&gt; stanza.</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">The namespace of the &lt;rtt/&gt; element is =
=E2=80=9Curn:xmpp:rtt:0=E2=80=9D.</p>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h3 id=3D"rtt_attributes">4.2 RTT Attributes<a cl=
ass=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#rtt_a=
ttributes"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the document">=C2=B6</abbr>=
</a></h3>
        <div class=3D"indent"><h4 id=3D"seq">4.2.1 seq<a class=3D"anchor-li=
nk" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#seq"><abbr title=3D"L=
ink to this point in the document">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h4>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">This REQUIRED attribute is a counter to mainta=
in synchronization of real-time text. Senders MUST increment this value by =
1 for each subsequent edit to the same real-time message, including when ap=
pending new text. Receiving clients MUST monitor this 'seq' value as a ligh=
tweight verification on the synchronization of real-time text messages. The=
 bounds of 'seq' is 31-bits, the range of positive values for a signed 32-b=
it integer. See <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#keepin=
g_realtime_text_synchronized">Keeping Real-Time Text Synchronized</a>.</p>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h4 id=3D"event">4.2.2 event<a class=3D"anchor-li=
nk" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#event"><abbr title=3D=
"Link to this point in the document">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h4>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">This attribute signals events for real-time te=
xt.</p>
        <figure class=3D"table"><figcaption id=3D"table-1"><strong>Table 1:=
</strong> <a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-=
0301.html#table-1"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the document">=C2=
=B6</abbr></a></figcaption><table>
          <tbody><tr class=3D"body">
            <th colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">event</th>
            <th colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">Description</th>
            <th colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">Action&nbsp;Elements</th>
            <th colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">Sender&nbsp;Support</th>
            <th colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">Recipient&nbsp;Support</th>
          </tr>
          <tr class=3D"body">
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">new</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">Begin a new real-time =
message.</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">Yes</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D""><strong>REQUIRED</stro=
ng></td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D""><strong>REQUIRED</stro=
ng></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class=3D"body">
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">reset</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">Re-initialize the real=
-time message.</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">Yes</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">RECOMMENDED</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D""><strong>REQUIRED</stro=
ng></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class=3D"body">
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">edit</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">Modify existing real-t=
ime message.</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">Yes</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">OPTIONAL</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D""><strong>REQUIRED</stro=
ng></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class=3D"body">
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">init</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">Signals activation of =
real-time text.</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">No</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">OPTIONAL</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">RECOMMENDED</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class=3D"body">
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">cancel</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">Signals deactivation o=
f real-time text.</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">No</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">OPTIONAL</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">RECOMMENDED</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody></table></figure>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">If the 'event' attribute is omitted, event=3D"=
edit" is assumed as the default. When <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extension=
s/xep-0301.html#action_elements">Action Elements</a> are used (e.g., text a=
ppends, insertions and deletions), the &lt;rtt/&gt; element MAY contain one=
 or more of any action elements, in any order. When action elements are not=
 allowed, the &lt;rtt/&gt; element MUST be empty. Recipient clients MUST ig=
nore &lt;rtt/&gt; elements containing unrecognized 'event' values.</p>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h4 id=3D"id">4.2.3 id<a class=3D"anchor-link" hr=
ef=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#id"><abbr title=3D"Link to =
this point in the document">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h4>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">This attribute is used only if <span class=3D"=
ref" style=3D""><a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0308.html">Last =
Message Correction (XEP-0308)</a></span>  [<a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/exte=
nsions/xep-0301.html#nt-idm45597907544640">9</a>] is implemented along with=
 this specification. See <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.ht=
ml#usage_with_last_message_correction">Usage with Last Message Correction</=
a> to enable real-time text during editing of the previous message.</p>
    </div>
</div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h3 id=3D"processing_rules">4.3 Processing Rules<=
a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#p=
rocessing_rules"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the document">=C2=B6<=
/abbr></a></h3>
      <ul class=3D"" style=3D"">
        <li class=3D"" style=3D""><p class=3D"" style=3D""><strong>Initiali=
ze a new real-time message: &lt;rtt event=3D"new"/&gt; and &lt;rtt event=3D=
"reset"/&gt;</strong></p>
          <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Sender clients MUST use an &lt;rtt/&gt; =
element containing either event=3D"new" or event=3D"reset" in the first tra=
nsmission of a new real-time message. Recipient clients MUST initialize a n=
ew blank real-time message for display, and then process all <a href=3D"htt=
ps://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#action_elements">Action Elements</a>=
 (e.g., text insertions and deletions) included within the &lt;rtt/&gt; ele=
ment. If a real-time message already exists from the same sender in the sam=
e chat session, its content MUST be seamlessly replaced (i.e., cleared prio=
r to immediately processing action elements).</p></li>
        <li class=3D"" style=3D""><p class=3D"" style=3D""><strong>Both &lt=
;rtt event=3D"new"/&gt; and &lt;rtt event=3D"reset"/&gt; are logically iden=
tical to recipients, except for presentation:</strong></p>
          <p class=3D"" style=3D"">For recipients, these differ only for op=
tional presentation purposes (e.g., highlighting newly started incoming mes=
sages). Senders SHOULD use event=3D"new" when sending the first text of a n=
ew message (e.g., the first key presses), and only use event=3D"reset" when=
 doing <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#message_refresh=
">Message Refresh</a> or <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.ht=
ml#simple_realtime_text">Simple Real-Time Text</a>. See <a href=3D"https://=
xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#keeping_realtime_text_synchronized">Keepi=
ng Real-Time Text Synchronized</a>.</p></li>
        <li class=3D"" style=3D""><p class=3D"" style=3D""><strong>Sending =
modifications of a real-time message: Outgoing &lt;rtt event=3D"edit"/&gt; =
or &lt;rtt/&gt;</strong></p>
          <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Sender clients SHOULD transmit this elem=
ent at a regular <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#trans=
mission_interval">Transmission Interval</a> while the message is being modi=
fied. The 'seq' attribute MUST increment by 1 for every consecutive modific=
ation transmitted. See <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html=
#sending_realtime_text">Sending Real-Time Text</a>.</p></li>
        <li class=3D"" style=3D""><p class=3D"" style=3D""><strong>Receivin=
g modifications of a real-time message: Incoming &lt;rtt event=3D"edit"/&gt=
; or &lt;rtt/&gt;</strong></p>
          <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Recipient clients must verify that the '=
seq' attribute increments by 1 in consecutively received &lt;rtt/&gt; eleme=
nts from the same sender. If 'seq' increments as expected, the <a href=3D"h=
ttps://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#action_elements">Action Elements</=
a> (e.g., text insertions and deletions) included with this element MUST be=
 processed to modify the existing real-time message. Otherwise, if 'seq' do=
es not increment as expected, or if no real-time message already exists, th=
e real-time message is considered out of sync and all subsequent modificati=
ons MUST be ignored until a new real-time message is initialized via event=
=3D"new" or event=3D"reset". See <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep=
-0301.html#keeping_realtime_text_synchronized">Keeping Real-Time Text Synch=
ronized</a>.</p></li>
        <li class=3D"" style=3D""><p class=3D"" style=3D""><strong>Committi=
ng a real-time message: Delivery of a &lt;body/&gt; element</strong></p>
          <p class=3D"" style=3D"">A real-time message is considered comple=
te upon receiving &lt;body/&gt;. See <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions=
/xep-0301.html#body_element">Body Element</a>.</p></li>
        <li class=3D"" style=3D""><p class=3D"" style=3D""><strong>Starting=
 real-time text: &lt;rtt event=3D"init"/&gt;</strong></p>
          <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Clients MAY use this value to signal act=
ivation of real-time text without first starting a real-time message, since=
 the sender may not start composing immediately. The 'seq' attribute is ign=
ored by recipient clients. See <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0=
301.html#guidelines_for_initiating_realtime_text">Guidelines for Initiating=
 Real-Time Text</a>.</p></li>
        <li class=3D"" style=3D""><p class=3D"" style=3D""><strong>Ending r=
eal-time text: &lt;rtt event=3D"cancel"/&gt;</strong></p>
          <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Clients MAY use this value to signal dea=
ctivation of real-time text. Clients receiving this element SHOULD also dis=
continue sending &lt;rtt/&gt; elements for the remainder of the same one-to=
-one chat session (until event=3D"init" is used again), and handle any unfi=
nished real-time messages appropriately (e.g., clearing or saving the messa=
ge). The 'seq' attribute is ignored by recipient clients. See <a href=3D"ht=
tps://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#guidelines_for_initiating_realtime_=
text">Guidelines for Initiating Real-Time Text</a>.</p></li>
        <li class=3D"" style=3D""><p class=3D"" style=3D""><strong>Starting=
 value for seq attribute:</strong></p>
          <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Sender clients MAY use any new starting =
value for 'seq' when initializing a real-time message using event=3D"new" o=
r event=3D"reset". Recipient clients receiving such elements MUST use this =
'seq' value as the new starting value. A random starting value is RECOMMEND=
ED to improve reliability of <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-030=
1.html#keeping_realtime_text_synchronized">Keeping Real-Time Text Synchroni=
zed</a> during <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#usage_w=
ith_multiuser_chat">Usage with Multi-User Chat</a> and <a href=3D"https://x=
mpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#simultaneous_logins">Simultaneous Logins</=
a>.</p></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h3 id=3D"body_element">4.4 Body Element<a class=
=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#body_ele=
ment"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the document">=C2=B6</abbr></a><=
/h3>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">The real-time message is considered complete u=
pon receipt of a standard &lt;body/&gt; element (as qualified by the 'jabbe=
r:client' namespace in <span class=3D"ref" style=3D""><a href=3D"http://too=
ls.ietf.org/html/rfc6121">XMPP IM</a></span>  [<a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/=
extensions/xep-0301.html#nt-idm45597907500624">10</a>]). The delivered text=
 within &lt;body/&gt; is considered the final message text, and supersedes =
the real-time message. In the ideal case, the text within &lt;body/&gt; is =
redundant since it is identical to the final contents of the real-time mess=
age.</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Sender clients MAY transmit the &lt;body/&gt; =
element in the same or separate &lt;message/&gt; stanza as the one containi=
ng the final &lt;rtt/&gt; element for the real-time message. To continue se=
nding real-time text in subsequent &lt;message/&gt; stanzas, the sender cli=
ent MUST first initialize a new real-time message according to <a href=3D"h=
ttps://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#processing_rules">Processing Rules=
</a>.</p>
        <div class=3D"indent"><h4 id=3D"backwards_compatible">4.4.1 Backwar=
ds Compatible<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/x=
ep-0301.html#backwards_compatible"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the=
 document">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h4>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">This real-time text standard simply provides e=
arly delivery of text before the &lt;body/&gt; element. The &lt;body/&gt; e=
lement continues to follow the XMPP IM specification. In particular, XMPP i=
mplementations need to ignore XML elements they do not understand. Clients,=
 that do not support real-time text, will continue to behave normally, disp=
laying complete lines of messages as they are delivered.</p>
    </div>
</div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h3 id=3D"transmission_interval">4.5 Transmission=
 Interval<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0=
301.html#transmission_interval"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the do=
cument">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h3>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">For the best balance between interoperability =
and usability, the default transmission interval of &lt;rtt/&gt; elements f=
or a continuously-changing message SHOULD be approximately <strong>700 mill=
iseconds</strong>. This interval makes it possible for clients to meet <str=
ong>ITU-T Rec. F.700</strong> Section A.3.2.1 for good quality real-time te=
xt conversation in many network environments. If a different transmission i=
nterval needs to be used, the interval SHOULD be <strong>between 300 and 10=
00 milliseconds</strong>.</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">A longer interval will lead to a less optimal =
user experience. Conversely, a much shorter interval can lead to <a href=3D=
"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#congestion_considerations">Conge=
stion Considerations</a>. To provide fluid real-time text, one or more of t=
he following methods can be used:</p>
    <ul class=3D"" style=3D"">
      <li class=3D"" style=3D""><a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-=
0301.html#preserving_key_press_intervals">Preserving Key Press Intervals</a=
> for natural typing display, independently of the transmission interval.</=
li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Use of <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensio=
ns/xep-0301.html#time_critical_and_low_latency_methods">Time Critical and L=
ow Latency Methods</a>, for real-time captioning/speech transcription.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">For other options or reduced-precision opti=
ons, see <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#lowbandwidth_=
and_lowprecision_text_smoothing">Low-Bandwidth and Low-Precision Text Smoot=
hing</a>.</li>
    </ul>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h3 id=3D"realtime_text_actions">4.6 Real-Time Te=
xt Actions<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-=
0301.html#realtime_text_actions"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the d=
ocument">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h3>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">The &lt;rtt/&gt; element MAY contain one or mo=
re <strong>action elements</strong> representing real-time text operations,=
 including text being appended, inserted, or deleted.</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Many chat clients allow a sender to edit their=
 message before sending (via a Send button, or pressing Enter). The seamles=
s inclusion of real-time text functionality, in existing client software, n=
eeds to preserve the sender's existing expectation of being able to edit th=
eir messages. In a chat session with real-time text, the recipient can see =
the sender compose and edit their message before it is completed.</p>
        <div class=3D"indent"><h4 id=3D"action_elements">4.6.1 Action Eleme=
nts<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.ht=
ml#action_elements"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the document">=C2=
=B6</abbr></a></h4>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">This is a short summary of action elements tha=
t operate on a real-time message.</p>
        <figure class=3D"table"><figcaption id=3D"table-2"><strong>Table 2:=
</strong> <a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-=
0301.html#table-2"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the document">=C2=
=B6</abbr></a></figcaption><table>
          <tbody><tr class=3D"body">
            <th colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">Action</th>
            <th colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">Element</th>
            <th colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">Description</th>
            <th colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">Sender&nbsp;Support</th>
            <th colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">Recipient&nbsp;Support</th>
          </tr>
          <tr class=3D"body">
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">Insert&nbsp;Text</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">&lt;t&nbsp;p=3D'#'&gt;=
text&lt;/t&gt;</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">Insert specified <stro=
ng>text</strong> at position 'p' in message.</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D""><strong>REQUIRED</stro=
ng></td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D""><strong>REQUIRED</stro=
ng></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class=3D"body">
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">Erase&nbsp;Text</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">&lt;e&nbsp;p=3D'#'&nbs=
p;n=3D'#'/&gt;</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">Remove 'n' characters =
before position 'p' in message<em>.</em></td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">RECOMMENDED</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D""><strong>REQUIRED</stro=
ng></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class=3D"body">
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">Wait&nbsp;Interval</td=
>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">&lt;w&nbsp;n=3D'#'/&gt=
;</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">Wait 'n' milliseconds.=
</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">RECOMMENDED</td>
            <td align=3D"" colspan=3D"" rowspan=3D"">RECOMMENDED</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody></table></figure>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">These elements are kept compact in order to sa=
ve bandwidth, since a single &lt;rtt/&gt; element can contain a large numbe=
r of action elements (e.g., during <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/x=
ep-0301.html#preserving_key_press_intervals">Preserving Key Press Intervals=
</a>). See <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#list_of_act=
ion_elements">List of Action Elements</a> for details.</p>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h4 id=3D"attribute_values">4.6.2 Attribute Value=
s<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html=
#attribute_values"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the document">=C2=
=B6</abbr></a></h4>
    <ul class=3D"" style=3D"">
      <li class=3D"" style=3D""><p class=3D"" style=3D"">For <a href=3D"htt=
ps://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#element_e_erase_text">Element &lt;e/=
&gt; =E2=80=93 Erase Text</a>:<br>
        The 'n' attribute is a length value, in number of characters. If 'n=
' is omitted, the default value of 'n' MUST be =E2=80=9C1=E2=80=9D.</p></li=
>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D""><p class=3D"" style=3D"">For <a href=3D"htt=
ps://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#element_t_insert_text">Element &lt;t=
/&gt; =E2=80=93 Insert Text</a> and <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/=
xep-0301.html#element_e_erase_text">Element &lt;e/&gt; =E2=80=93 Erase Text=
</a>:<br>
        The 'p' attribute is an absolute position value, as a character pos=
ition index into the real-time message, where =E2=80=9C0=E2=80=9D represent=
s the beginning of the message. If 'p' is omitted, the default value of 'p'=
 MUST point to the end of the message (i.e., 'p' is set to the current leng=
th of the real-time message).</p></li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D""><p class=3D"" style=3D"">For the purpose of=
 this specification, the word "character" represents a single Unicode code =
point. See <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#unicode_cha=
racter_counting">Unicode Character Counting</a>.</p></li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D""><p class=3D"" style=3D"">Senders MUST NOT u=
se negative values for any attribute, nor use 'p' values bigger than the cu=
rrent message length. However, recipients receiving such values MUST clip n=
egative values to =E2=80=9C0=E2=80=9D, and clip excessively high 'p' values=
 to the current length of the real-time message. Modifications only occur w=
ithin the boundaries of the current real-time message.</p></li>
    </ul>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h4 id=3D"list_of_action_elements">4.6.3 List of =
Action Elements<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions=
/xep-0301.html#list_of_action_elements"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point i=
n the document">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h4>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Recipients MUST be able to process all &lt;t/&=
gt; and &lt;e/&gt; action elements for incoming &lt;rtt/&gt; transmissions,=
 even if senders do not use all of these for outgoing &lt;rtt/&gt; transmis=
sions (e.g., <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#simple_re=
altime_text">Simple Real-Time Text</a>). Support for &lt;w/&gt; is RECOMMEN=
DED for both senders and recipients, in order to accommodate <a href=3D"htt=
ps://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#preserving_key_press_intervals">Pres=
erving Key Press Intervals</a>. Recipients MUST ignore unexpected or unsupp=
orted elements within &lt;rtt/&gt;, while continuing to process subsequent =
action elements. Compatibility is ensured via <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/e=
xtensions/xep-0301.html#namespace_versioning">Namespace Versioning</a>. Act=
ion elements are immediate child elements of the &lt;rtt/&gt; element, and =
are never nested. See examples in <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xe=
p-0301.html#use_cases">Use Cases</a>.</p>
        <div class=3D"indent"><h5 id=3D"element_t_insert_text">4.6.3.1 Elem=
ent &lt;t/&gt; =E2=80=93 Insert Text</h5>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Supports the transmission of text, including k=
ey presses, and text block inserts.<br>
    <em>Note: Text can be any</em> <em>subset of text allowed in the &lt;bo=
dy/&gt; element of a &lt;message/&gt;. If &lt;t/&gt; is empty or blank, no =
text modification takes place.</em></p>
    <figure class=3D"code"><figcaption></figcaption><pre class=3D"prettypri=
nt prettyprinted" style=3D""><span class=3D"tag">&lt;t&gt;</span><span clas=
s=3D"pln">text</span><span class=3D"tag">&lt;/t&gt;</span></pre></figure>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Append specified <strong>text</strong> at the =
end of message. ('p' defaults to message length).<br>
    <em>Note: This action element is the minimum support REQUIRED for sende=
r clients (i.e., speech transcription, chat bots, and <a href=3D"https://xm=
pp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#simple_realtime_text">Simple Real-Time Text=
</a> are still possible without supporting additional action elements).</em=
></p>
    <figure class=3D"code"><figcaption></figcaption><pre class=3D"prettypri=
nt prettyprinted" style=3D""><span class=3D"tag">&lt;t</span><span class=3D=
"pln"> </span><span class=3D"atn">p</span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</span><sp=
an class=3D"atv">'#'</span><span class=3D"tag">&gt;</span><span class=3D"pl=
n">text</span><span class=3D"tag">&lt;/t&gt;</span></pre></figure>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Inserts specified <strong>text</strong> at pos=
ition 'p' in the message text.</p>



    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h5 id=3D"element_e_erase_text">4.6.3.2 Element &=
lt;e/&gt; =E2=80=93 Erase Text</h5>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Supports the behavior of backspace key presses=
. Text is removed towards beginning of the message. This element is also us=
ed for all delete operations, including the backspace key, the delete key, =
and text block deletes.<br>
    <em>Note: Excess backspaces MUST be ignored by the receiving client. Th=
us, text is backspaced only to the beginning of the message, in situations =
where n is larger than p.</em></p>
    <figure class=3D"code"><figcaption></figcaption><pre class=3D"prettypri=
nt prettyprinted" style=3D""><span class=3D"tag">&lt;e/&gt;</span></pre></f=
igure>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Remove 1 character from end of message. ('n' d=
efaults to =E2=80=9C1=E2=80=9D, and 'p' defaults to message length)</p>
    <figure class=3D"code"><figcaption></figcaption><pre class=3D"prettypri=
nt prettyprinted" style=3D""><span class=3D"tag">&lt;e</span><span class=3D=
"pln"> </span><span class=3D"atn">p</span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</span><sp=
an class=3D"atv">'#'</span><span class=3D"tag">/&gt;</span></pre></figure>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Remove 1 character before character position '=
p' in message. ('n' defaults to =E2=80=9C1=E2=80=9D)</p>
    <figure class=3D"code"><figcaption></figcaption><pre class=3D"prettypri=
nt prettyprinted" style=3D""><span class=3D"tag">&lt;e</span><span class=3D=
"pln"> </span><span class=3D"atn">n</span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</span><sp=
an class=3D"atv">'#'</span><span class=3D"tag">/&gt;</span></pre></figure>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Remove 'n' characters from end of message. ('p=
' defaults to message length)</p>
    <figure class=3D"code"><figcaption></figcaption><pre class=3D"prettypri=
nt prettyprinted" style=3D""><span class=3D"tag">&lt;e</span><span class=3D=
"pln"> </span><span class=3D"atn">n</span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</span><sp=
an class=3D"atv">'#'</span><span class=3D"pln"> </span><span class=3D"atn">=
p</span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</span><span class=3D"atv">'#'</span><span c=
lass=3D"tag">/&gt;</span></pre></figure>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Remove 'n' characters before character positio=
n 'p' in message.</p>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h5 id=3D"element_w_wait_interval">4.6.3.3 Elemen=
t &lt;w/&gt; =E2=80=93 Wait Interval</h5>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Allow for the transmission of intervals, betwe=
en real-time text actions, to recreate the pauses between key presses. See =
<a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#preserving_key_press_i=
ntervals">Preserving Key Press Intervals</a>.</p>
    <figure class=3D"code"><figcaption></figcaption><pre class=3D"prettypri=
nt prettyprinted" style=3D""><span class=3D"tag">&lt;w</span><span class=3D=
"pln"> </span><span class=3D"atn">n</span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</span><sp=
an class=3D"atv">'#'</span><span class=3D"tag">/&gt;</span></pre></figure>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Wait 'n' milliseconds before processing the ne=
xt action element. This pause MAY be approximate, and not necessarily be of=
 millisecond precision. Sender clients SHOULD NOT send large 'n' values tha=
t exceed the average <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#t=
ransmission_interval">Transmission Interval</a>. Recipient clients MAY sele=
ctively shorten or ignore the pauses ('n') in &lt;w/&gt; action elements to=
 avoid lag in a chat session. Situations such as network congestion can res=
ult in a surge of &lt;w/&gt; elements where the total of pauses exceeds a t=
ransmission interval cycle. See <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-=
0301.html#receiving_realtime_text">Receiving Real-Time Text</a>.</p>
    </div>
</div>
</div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h3 id=3D"keeping_realtime_text_synchronized">4.7=
 Keeping Real-Time Text Synchronized<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https:=
//xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#keeping_realtime_text_synchronized"><ab=
br title=3D"Link to this point in the document">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h3>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">During a chat session, real-time text needs to=
 be identical on both the sender and recipient ends. A missing &lt;rtt/&gt;=
 transmission can represent missing text or missing edits. Also, recipients=
 can connect after the sender has already started composing a message. To a=
ddress this, a <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#message=
_refresh">Message Refresh</a> mechanism allows recipient clients to recover=
 the sender's real-time message that is actively in-progress. This synchron=
izes real-time text in many situations, including:</p>
    <ul class=3D"" style=3D"">
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">After recipient client reconnections (e.g.,=
 due to wireless reception, due to user restarting client).</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">After recipient client discarded <a href=3D=
"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#stale_messages">Stale Messages</=
a> (e.g., sender resumes composing hours later).</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D""><a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-=
0301.html#simultaneous_logins">Simultaneous Logins</a> (e.g., user switchin=
g between devices/clients or between windows/tabs in a client).</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">During <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensio=
ns/xep-0301.html#usage_with_multiuser_chat">Usage with Multi-User Chat</a> =
(e.g., participants joining/leaving while other participants are composing)=
.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">After message stanzas are lost in transit (=
e.g., <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#congestion_consi=
derations">Congestion Considerations</a>).</li>
    </ul>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Recipient clients MUST keep track of separate =
real-time messages on a per-contact basis, including tracking independent '=
<a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#seq">seq</a>' attribut=
e values. Recipient clients MAY track incoming &lt;rtt/&gt; elements per ba=
re JID &lt;localpart@domain.tld&gt; to keep only one real-time message per =
contact. The remainder of this section automatically handles conflicting &l=
t;rtt/&gt; elements (e.g., typing coming concurrently from separate <a href=
=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#simultaneous_logins">Simultan=
eous Logins</a>, contrary to the common case of one typist per contact). Al=
ternatively, recipient clients MAY track incoming &lt;rtt/&gt; elements per=
 full JID &lt;localpart@domain.tld/resource&gt; and/or per &lt;thread/&gt;,=
 to keep multiple separate real-time messages for the same contact. For mor=
e information about &lt;thread/&gt;, see <span class=3D"ref" style=3D""><a =
href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0201.html">Best Practices for Messa=
ge Threads (XEP-0201)</a></span>  [<a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/x=
ep-0301.html#nt-idm45597907388720">11</a>].</p>
        <div class=3D"indent"><h4 id=3D"staying_in_sync">4.7.1 Staying In S=
ync<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.ht=
ml#staying_in_sync"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the document">=C2=
=B6</abbr></a></h4>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">By following <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/exten=
sions/xep-0301.html#processing_rules">Processing Rules</a>, the recipient c=
lient creates a new real-time message when receiving &lt;rtt event=3D"new"/=
&gt; or &lt;rtt event=3D"reset"/&gt;. Thereafter, when receiving text modif=
ications (i.e., &lt;rtt event=3D"edit"/&gt; or &lt;rtt/&gt; without an 'eve=
nt' attribute):</p>
    <ol start=3D"" class=3D"" style=3D"">
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">There MUST be an existing real-time message=
 (created via &lt;rtt event=3D"new"/&gt; or &lt;rtt event=3D"reset"/&gt;);<=
/li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Senders MUST increment the 'seq' attribute =
in steps of 1, for consecutively transmitted text modifications.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Recipients MUST verify that the 'seq' attri=
bute is incrementing by 1, for consecutively received text modifications.</=
li>
    </ol>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h4 id=3D"recovery_from_loss_of_sync">4.7.2 Recov=
ery From Loss of Sync<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/exte=
nsions/xep-0301.html#recovery_from_loss_of_sync"><abbr title=3D"Link to thi=
s point in the document">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h4>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Loss of sync occurs during receiving text modi=
fications if the 'seq' attribute does not increment by 1 as expected, or if=
 no real-time message exists. In this case:</p>
    <ul class=3D"" style=3D"">
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Recipients MUST keep the real-time message =
unchanged (if any exists); and</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Recipients MUST ignore subsequent text modi=
fications (i.e., &lt;rtt event=3D"edit"/&gt; or &lt;rtt/&gt; without an 'ev=
ent' attribute); and</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">An indication can be used to show the loss =
of sync (e.g., color coding, modified chat state message).</li>
    </ul>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Recovery occurs when the recipient receives th=
e following:</p>
    <ul class=3D"" style=3D"">
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">A &lt;body/&gt; element. The <a href=3D"htt=
ps://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#body_element">Body Element</a> super=
sedes the real-time message.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">An &lt;rtt/&gt; element with an 'event' att=
ribute of 'new' or 'reset' (e.g., new message, or <a href=3D"https://xmpp.o=
rg/extensions/xep-0301.html#message_refresh">Message Refresh</a>).</li>
    </ul>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h4 id=3D"message_refresh">4.7.3 Message Refresh<=
a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#m=
essage_refresh"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the document">=C2=B6</=
abbr></a></h4>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">A message refresh is the sender's partially co=
mposed text being (re)transmitted via &lt;rtt event=3D"reset"/&gt;. The rec=
ipient client(s) can seamlessly redisplay the real-time message as a result=
. This allows real-time text to resume quickly, without waiting for senders=
 to start a new message:</p>
    <figure class=3D"code"><figcaption></figcaption><pre class=3D"prettypri=
nt prettyprinted" style=3D""><span class=3D"tag">&lt;rtt</span><span class=
=3D"pln"> </span><span class=3D"atn">event</span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</s=
pan><span class=3D"atv">'reset'</span><span class=3D"pln"> </span><span cla=
ss=3D"atn">seq</span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</span><span class=3D"atv">'#'<=
/span><span class=3D"pln"> </span><span class=3D"atn">xmlns</span><span cla=
ss=3D"pun">=3D</span><span class=3D"atv">'urn:xmpp:rtt:0'</span><span class=
=3D"tag">&gt;</span><span class=3D"pln">
  </span><span class=3D"tag">&lt;t&gt;</span><span class=3D"pln">This is a =
retransmission of the entire real-time message.</span><span class=3D"tag">&=
lt;/t&gt;</span><span class=3D"pln">
</span><span class=3D"tag">&lt;/rtt&gt;</span></pre></figure>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">The message refresh SHOULD be transmitted at i=
ntervals during active typing or composing. The RECOMMENDED interval is 10 =
seconds. This interval is frequent enough to minimize user waiting time, wh=
ile being infrequent enough to not cause a significant bandwidth overhead. =
This interval can be varied, or be set to a longer time period, in order to=
 reduce average bandwidth (e.g., long messages, infrequent or minor message=
 changes). To save bandwidth, message refreshes SHOULD NOT occur continuous=
ly while the sender is idle. To allow quicker resumption of real-time text,=
 sender clients MAY adjust the timing of the message refresh to occur right=
 after any of the following additional events:</p>
    <ul class=3D"" style=3D"">
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">When the recipient starts sending messages =
from a different full JID (e.g., switched clients);</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">When the recipient presence changes to a mo=
re available state (e.g., &lt;show/&gt; value of =E2=80=9Cchat=E2=80=9D);</=
li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">When the sender resumes composing after an =
extended pause (e.g., recipient may have cleared <a href=3D"https://xmpp.or=
g/extensions/xep-0301.html#stale_messages">Stale Messages</a>);</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">When the conversation is unlocked (e.g., se=
ction 5.1 of XMPP IM);</li>
    </ul>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">If the recipient already has an existing real-=
time message from the sender, <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-03=
01.html#processing_rules">Processing Rules</a> require that the real-time m=
essage MUST be seamlessly replaced. Thus, if the recipient is successfully =
<a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#staying_in_sync">Stayi=
ng In Sync</a>, the recipient user sees no visible effect since the text co=
ntained within &lt;rtt event=3D"reset"/&gt; is a duplicate of the existing =
real-time message. If the recipient client was out of sync (<a href=3D"http=
s://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#recovery_from_loss_of_sync">Recovery =
From Loss of Sync</a>) or it has no real-time message, the recipient user s=
ees the real-time message immediately =E2=80=9Ccatch up=E2=80=9D.</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Note: The use of &lt;rtt event=3D"reset"/&gt; =
is not limited to message refresh, as it can contain any number of <a href=
=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#action_elements">Action Eleme=
nts</a> in any order. Sender clients MAY combine a message refresh with add=
itional action elements (e.g., re-transmitting a whole message in one <a hr=
ef=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#element_t_insert_text">Elem=
ent &lt;t/&gt; =E2=80=93 Insert Text</a>, followed by some additional actio=
n elements, such as additional typing or backspacing, to seamlessly allow <=
a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#preserving_key_press_in=
tervals">Preserving Key Press Intervals</a>).</p>
    </div>
</div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h3 id=3D"accurate_processing_of_action_elements"=
>4.8 Accurate Processing of Action Elements<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D=
"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#accurate_processing_of_action_el=
ements"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the document">=C2=B6</abbr></a=
></h3>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Real-time text is generated based on text norm=
ally allowed to be transmitted within the &lt;body/&gt; element.</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Incorrectly generated <a href=3D"https://xmpp.=
org/extensions/xep-0301.html#action_elements">Action Elements</a> and <a hr=
ef=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#attribute_values">Attribute=
 Values</a> can lead to inconsistencies between the sender and recipient du=
ring real-time editing. The Unicode characters of the real-time text need t=
o be transmitted unaltered from the sender to the recipient, without unexpe=
cted modifications after sender pre-processing. This is the chain between t=
he sender's creation of real-time text, to the recipient's processing of re=
al-time text. Unaltered transmission of Unicode characters is possible with=
 sender pre-processing, as long as the transmission from the sender to the =
recipient remains standards-compliant, including compliant XML processors a=
nd compliant XMPP servers.</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">If unexpected Unicode inconsistencies occur du=
ring real-time message editing, the recipient client will normally recover =
the message upon receiving a <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-030=
1.html#body_element">Body Element</a> or a <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/exte=
nsions/xep-0301.html#message_refresh">Message Refresh</a>.</p>
        <div class=3D"indent"><h4 id=3D"unicode_character_counting">4.8.1 U=
nicode Character Counting<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/=
extensions/xep-0301.html#unicode_character_counting"><abbr title=3D"Link to=
 this point in the document">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h4>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">For this specification, a "character" represen=
ts a single Unicode code point. This is the same definition used in section=
 1.1 of <span class=3D"ref" style=3D""><strong><a href=3D"http://tools.ietf=
.org/html/rfc5198">RFC 5198</a></strong></span>
   [<a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#nt-idm455979073376=
16">12</a>]. For platform-independent interoperability of <a href=3D"https:=
//xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#action_elements">Action Elements</a>, c=
alculations on <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#attribu=
te_values">Attribute Values</a> (<em><strong>p</strong></em> and <em><stron=
g>n</strong></em>) MUST be based on counts of Unicode code points.</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Many platforms use different internal encoding=
s (i.e., string formats) that are different from the transmission encoding =
(UTF-8). These factors need to be considered:</p>
    <ul class=3D"" style=3D"">
      <li class=3D"" style=3D""><p class=3D"" style=3D"">Multiple Unicode c=
ode points (e.g., combining marks, accents) can form a combining character =
sequence. This can occur in situations where there isn't a visually equival=
ent composite character of a single code point (e.g., when doing Unicode no=
rmalization).<br>
        <em>Action elements operate on Unicode code points individually.</e=
m></p></li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D""><p class=3D"" style=3D"">Unicode code point=
s U+10000 through U+10FFFF are represented as a surrogate pair in some Unic=
ode encodings (e.g., UTF-16).<br>
        <em>Action elements operate on Unicode code points as a whole, not =
on separate components of a surrogate pair.</em></p></li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D""><p class=3D"" style=3D"">XMPP transmission =
uses UTF-8, which uses a variable number of bytes per Unicode code point.<b=
r><em>Action elements operate on Unicode code points as a whole, not on sep=
arate bytes.</em></p></li>
    </ul>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Lengths and positions in <a href=3D"https://xm=
pp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#attribute_values">Attribute Values</a> are =
relative to the internal Unicode text of the real-time message, independent=
ly of the directionality of actual displayed text. As a result, any valid U=
nicode text direction can be used with real-time text (right-to-left, left-=
to-right, and bidirectional). One way for implementers to visualize this, i=
s to simply visualize Unicode text as an array of individual code points, a=
nd treat <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#attribute_val=
ues">Attribute Values</a> as array indexes.</p>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h4 id=3D"guidelines_for_senders">4.8.2 Guideline=
s for Senders<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/x=
ep-0301.html#guidelines_for_senders"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in t=
he document">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h4>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Sender clients MUST generate real-time text (<=
a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#action_elements">Action=
 Elements</a> and <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#attr=
ibute_values">Attribute Values</a>) based on the plain text version of the =
sender's message with pre-processing completed. This is separate from and c=
oncurrent to any displayed presentation of the same message (e.g., formatti=
ng, emoticon graphics, <span class=3D"ref" style=3D""><a href=3D"https://xm=
pp.org/extensions/xep-0071.html">XHTML-IM (XEP-0071)</a></span>  [<a href=
=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#nt-idm45597907315616">13</a>]=
).</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Pre-processing before generating real-time tex=
t includes Unicode normalization, conversion of emoticons graphics to text,=
 removal of illegal characters, line-break conversion, and any other necess=
ary text modifications. For Unicode normalization, sender clients SHOULD en=
sure the message is in <span class=3D"ref" style=3D""><strong><a href=3D"ht=
tp://www.unicode.org/reports/tr15/">Unicode Normalization Form C</a></stron=
g></span>
   [<a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#nt-idm455979073102=
40">14</a>] ("NFC"), as recommended within section 3 of <strong>RFC 5198</s=
trong>, and within many other standards such as Canonical XML 1.0.</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">If Unicode combining character sequences (e.g.=
, letter with multiple accents) are used for <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/ex=
tensions/xep-0301.html#element_t_insert_text">Element &lt;t/&gt; =E2=80=93 =
Insert Text</a>, then complete combining character sequences SHOULD be sent=
. In situations where modifications are required to an existing combining c=
haracter sequence (e.g., adding an additional accent), an <a href=3D"https:=
//xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#element_e_erase_text">Element &lt;e/&gt=
; =E2=80=93 Erase Text</a> SHOULD be used to delete the existing combining =
character sequence, before transmitting a complete replacement sequence via=
 the &lt;t/&gt; element. (However, recipients SHOULD NOT assume this behavi=
or from sending clients. See <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-030=
1.html#guidelines_for_recipients">Guidelines for Recipients</a>.)</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">For the purpose of calculating <a href=3D"http=
s://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#attribute_values">Attribute Values</a=
>, any line breaks MUST be treated as a single character. Conversion of lin=
e breaks into a single LINE FEED U+000A is REQUIRED for XML processors, acc=
ording to section 2.11 of <span class=3D"ref" style=3D""><strong><a href=3D=
"http://www.w3.org/TR/xml/">XML</a></strong></span>
   [<a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#nt-idm455979073014=
40">15</a>].</p>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h4 id=3D"guidelines_for_recipients">4.8.3 Guidel=
ines for Recipients<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extens=
ions/xep-0301.html#guidelines_for_recipients"><abbr title=3D"Link to this p=
oint in the document">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h4>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">For <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep=
-0301.html#element_t_insert_text">Element &lt;t/&gt; =E2=80=93 Insert Text<=
/a>, text MUST be obtained using compliant XML processing (including entiti=
es converted to characters). Recipient clients SHOULD ensure that the recei=
ved text is in Unicode Normalization Form C ("NFC"). After this, recipient =
clients MUST NOT do any other modifications to resulting real-time messages=
. This is to allow accurate processing of subsequent <a href=3D"https://xmp=
p.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#action_elements">Action Elements</a> and <a =
href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#attribute_values">Attribu=
te Values</a> (the recipient client can separately process/modify a copy of=
 the same real-time message text, if necessary for the purpose of display p=
resentation).</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">It is possible for sender clients to send <a h=
ref=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#element_t_insert_text">Ele=
ment &lt;t/&gt; =E2=80=93 Insert Text</a> with an incomplete combining char=
acter sequence (e.g., combining mark(s) without a Unicode base character). =
This is valid when extending an existing combining character sequence into =
a longer valid complete combining character sequence (e.g., adding an addit=
ional accent mark). It is also possible for senders to send <a href=3D"http=
s://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#element_e_erase_text">Element &lt;e/&=
gt; =E2=80=93 Erase Text</a> to remove code points from an existing combini=
ng character sequence, into a shorter valid complete combining character se=
quence (e.g., removing an accent mark). In all cases, recipient clients MUS=
T process these elements in accordance to <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/exten=
sions/xep-0301.html#action_elements">Action Elements</a>.</p>
    </div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"determining_support">5.
       Determining Support<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org=
/extensions/xep-0301.html#determining_support"><abbr title=3D"Link to this =
point in the document">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h2>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">If a client supports this real-time text proto=
col, it MUST advertise that fact in its responses to <span class=3D"ref" st=
yle=3D""><a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0030.html">Service Disc=
overy (XEP-0030)</a></span>  [<a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-03=
01.html#nt-idm45597907286816">16</a>] information requests ("disco#info") b=
y returning a feature of =E2=80=98<strong>urn:xmpp:rtt:0</strong>=E2=80=99.=
</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D""><strong>Example 1. A disco#info query</strong>=
</p>
    <figure class=3D"code"><figcaption></figcaption><pre class=3D"prettypri=
nt prettyprinted" style=3D""><span class=3D"tag">&lt;iq</span><span class=
=3D"pln"> </span><span class=3D"atn">from</span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</sp=
an><span class=3D"atv">'romeo@montague.lit/orchard'</span><span class=3D"pl=
n">
    </span><span class=3D"atn">id</span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</span><span=
 class=3D"atv">'disco1'</span><span class=3D"pln">
    </span><span class=3D"atn">to</span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</span><span=
 class=3D"atv">'juliet@capulet.lit/balcony'</span><span class=3D"pln">
    </span><span class=3D"atn">type</span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</span><sp=
an class=3D"atv">'get'</span><span class=3D"tag">&gt;</span><span class=3D"=
pln">
  </span><span class=3D"tag">&lt;query</span><span class=3D"pln"> </span><s=
pan class=3D"atn">xmlns</span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</span><span class=3D"=
atv">'http://jabber.org/protocol/disco#info'</span><span class=3D"tag">/&gt=
;</span><span class=3D"pln">
</span><span class=3D"tag">&lt;/iq&gt;</span><span class=3D"pln">
</span></pre></figure>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D""><strong>Example 2. A disco#info response</stro=
ng></p>
    <figure class=3D"code"><figcaption></figcaption><pre class=3D"prettypri=
nt prettyprinted" style=3D""><span class=3D"tag">&lt;iq</span><span class=
=3D"pln"> </span><span class=3D"atn">from</span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</sp=
an><span class=3D"atv">'juliet@capulet.lit/balcony'</span><span class=3D"pl=
n">
    </span><span class=3D"atn">id</span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</span><span=
 class=3D"atv">'disco1'</span><span class=3D"pln">
    </span><span class=3D"atn">to</span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</span><span=
 class=3D"atv">'romeo@montague.lit/orchard'</span><span class=3D"pln">
    </span><span class=3D"atn">type</span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</span><sp=
an class=3D"atv">'result'</span><span class=3D"tag">&gt;</span><span class=
=3D"pln">
  </span><span class=3D"tag">&lt;query</span><span class=3D"pln"> </span><s=
pan class=3D"atn">xmlns</span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</span><span class=3D"=
atv">'http://jabber.org/protocol/disco#info'</span><span class=3D"tag">&gt;=
</span><span class=3D"pln">
    </span><span class=3D"tag">&lt;feature</span><span class=3D"pln"> </spa=
n><span class=3D"atn">var</span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</span><span class=
=3D"atv">'urn:xmpp:rtt:0'</span><span class=3D"tag">/&gt;</span><span class=
=3D"pln">
  </span><span class=3D"tag">&lt;/query&gt;</span><span class=3D"pln">
</span><span class=3D"tag">&lt;/iq&gt;</span><span class=3D"pln">
</span></pre></figure>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">In order for an application to determine wheth=
er an entity supports this protocol, where possible it SHOULD use the dynam=
ic, presence-based profile of service discovery defined in <span class=3D"r=
ef" style=3D""><a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0115.html">Entity=
 Capabilities (XEP-0115)</a></span>  [<a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extension=
s/xep-0301.html#nt-idm45597907275360">17</a>]. However, if an application h=
as not received entity capabilities information from an entity, it SHOULD u=
se explicit service discovery instead.</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">See <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep=
-0301.html#guidelines_for_initiating_realtime_text">Guidelines for Initiati=
ng Real-Time Text</a> for more information, including implicit discovery.</=
p>
        <div class=3D"indent"><h3 id=3D"support_for_groupchat">5.1 Support =
for Groupchat<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/x=
ep-0301.html#support_for_groupchat"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in th=
e document">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h3>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Real-time text MAY also be used with <strong>M=
ulti-User Chat</strong>. Before transmitting &lt;rtt/&gt; elements to a gro=
upchat room, clients MUST follow section 17.1.1 of <strong>XEP-0045</strong=
> to verify that the service allows any extension or that =E2=80=98urn:xmpp=
:rtt:0=E2=80=99 is listed as an allowable namespace.</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Services explicitly allowing this extension MU=
ST follow section 17.1.1 of <strong>XEP-0045</strong> to include =E2=80=98u=
rn:xmpp:rtt:0=E2=80=99 as an allowable namespace.</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">See <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep=
-0301.html#usage_with_multiuser_chat">Usage with Multi-User Chat</a>.</p>
    </div>
<h2 id=3D"guidelines_for_initiating_realtime_text">6.
       Guidelines for Initiating Real-Time Text<a class=3D"anchor-link" hre=
f=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#guidelines_for_initiating_re=
altime_text"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the document">=C2=B6</abb=
r></a></h2>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Some clients can choose to send outgoing real-=
time text at all times by default. Other clients might choose to do user-in=
itiated activation (e.g., via a button). These guidelines provide interoper=
ability between clients that use different methods of initiating real-time =
text.</p>
        <div class=3D"indent"><h3 id=3D"activating_realtime_text">6.1 Activ=
ating Real-Time Text<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/exten=
sions/xep-0301.html#activating_realtime_text"><abbr title=3D"Link to this p=
oint in the document">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h3>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">In the simplest case, sender clients MAY simpl=
y begin transmitting real-time text (i.e., send &lt;rtt/&gt; elements) upon=
 determining support.</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">For one-to-one chats, it can be beneficial for=
 clients to easily synchronize the enabling/disabling of real-time text. Up=
on receiving incoming real-time text, recipient clients MAY automatically d=
o an appropriate response, such as:</p>
    <ul class=3D"" style=3D"">
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Activate immediately (begin transmitting &l=
t;rtt/&gt; elements too); or</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Activate after user confirmation prompt (fo=
r <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#privacy">Privacy</a>=
 considerations); or</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Deny (transmit &lt;rtt event=3D"cancel"/&gt=
;); or</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Ignore (discard incoming &lt;rtt/&gt; eleme=
nts); or</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Display only incoming real-time text (e.g.,=
 <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#usage_with_multiuser_=
chat">Usage with Multi-User Chat</a> participants control their own outgoin=
g real-time text).</li>
    </ul>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">To prevent transmission loops, senders SHOULD =
NOT transmit &lt;rtt event=3D"init"/&gt; automatically in response to incom=
ing &lt;rtt event=3D"init"/&gt;. Upon sending any &lt;rtt/&gt; elements (ex=
cept &lt;rtt event=3D"cancel"/&gt;), real-time text is considered activated=
 on the sender side and it is not necessary to transmit &lt;rtt event=3D"in=
it"/&gt; again for the chat session while real-time text is active.</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">For any client, the preferred first &lt;rtt/&g=
t; element to send is &lt;rtt <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-03=
01.html#event">event</a>=3D"init"/&gt; as it can quickly signal activation =
of real-time text, without waiting for the sender to begin composing a new =
message, and since it is usable regardless of discovery. Also, if the sende=
r was already composing a message when activating real-time text, <a href=
=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#message_refresh">Message Refr=
esh</a> handles this situation.</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">While explicit discovery is REQUIRED where pos=
sible (see <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#determining=
_support">Determining Support</a>), it is not possible to use explicit disc=
overy when the sender does not share a presence subscription with the the c=
ontact and knows only their bare JID (e.g., they have yet to receive stanza=
s from the contact). In this case, the sender client MAY implicitly request=
 and discover the use of real-time text, by sending &lt;rtt event=3D"init"/=
&gt; upon activation. Senders SHOULD NOT send any further &lt;rtt/&gt; elem=
ents, until support is confirmed either by incoming &lt;rtt/&gt; elements o=
r via discovery. Implicit discovery makes it possible to use real-time text=
 as an enhancement to <span class=3D"ref" style=3D""><a href=3D"https://xmp=
p.org/extensions/xep-0085.html">Chat State Notifications (XEP-0085)</a></sp=
an>  [<a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#nt-idm4559790724=
2576">18</a>] (Section 5.1), during all situations where it can be used (e.=
g., when an actively-composing sender appears invisible/offline to the reci=
pient). See <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#usage_with=
_chat_states">Usage with Chat States</a>.</p>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h3 id=3D"deactivating_realtime_text">6.2 Deactiv=
ating Real-Time Text<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/exten=
sions/xep-0301.html#deactivating_realtime_text"><abbr title=3D"Link to this=
 point in the document">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h3>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Real-time text MAY be deactivated by transmitt=
ing &lt;rtt <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#event">eve=
nt</a>=3D"cancel"/&gt;, or simply by ending the chat session. Recipient cli=
ents SHOULD respond to deactivation with appropriate response(s), including=
:</p>
    <ul class=3D"" style=3D"">
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Stop transmitting &lt;rtt/&gt; elements as =
well (not applicable to <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.htm=
l#usage_with_multiuser_chat">Usage with Multi-User Chat</a>); and</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Handle the sender's unfinished incoming rea=
l-time message; and</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Inform the recipient user that sender ended=
 real-time text (or denied/cancelled, if no real-time text was received).</=
li>
    </ul>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Any client MAY also send an &lt;rtt event=3D"c=
ancel"/&gt; when ending the chat session (e.g., user closes a chat window) =
or when deactivating real-time text while continuing the chat session. Clie=
nts receiving &lt;rtt event=3D"cancel"/&gt; do not need to also transmit &l=
t;rtt event=3D"cancel"/&gt; back.</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Senders deactivating real-time text while in t=
he middle of composing a message can continue composing their message witho=
ut real-time text being sent. Completed messages continue to be transmitted=
 normally via the <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#body=
_element">Body Element</a>. Recipients that no longer receive further real-=
time updates, MAY handle the incomplete sender's real-time message appropri=
ately (e.g., clearing/greying-out/saving the message, or using <a href=3D"h=
ttps://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#stale_messages">Stale Messages</a>=
 handling).</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">After deactivation, any client MAY reactivate =
real-time text again using &lt;rtt event=3D"init"/&gt;.</p>
    </div>
<h2 id=3D"implementation_notes">7.
       Implementation Notes<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.or=
g/extensions/xep-0301.html#implementation_notes"><abbr title=3D"Link to thi=
s point in the document">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h2>
        <div class=3D"indent"><h3 id=3D"text_presentation">7.1 Text Present=
ation<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.=
html#text_presentation"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the document">=
=C2=B6</abbr></a></h3>
        <div class=3D"indent"><h4 id=3D"avoid_bursty_text_presentation">7.1=
.1 Avoid Bursty Text Presentation<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://x=
mpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#avoid_bursty_text_presentation"><abbr titl=
e=3D"Link to this point in the document">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h4>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">If a long <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensio=
ns/xep-0301.html#transmission_interval">Transmission Interval</a> is used w=
ithout <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#preserving_key_=
press_intervals">Preserving Key Press Intervals</a>, then incoming text wil=
l appear in intermittent bursts if the display of text is not smoothed. Thi=
s hurts user experience of real-time text.</p>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h4 id=3D"preserving_key_press_intervals">7.1.2 P=
reserving Key Press Intervals<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.=
org/extensions/xep-0301.html#preserving_key_press_intervals"><abbr title=3D=
"Link to this point in the document">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h4>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">For high quality presentation of real-time tex=
t, the original look-and-feel of typing can be preserved independently of t=
he transmission interval. This is achieved using <a href=3D"https://xmpp.or=
g/extensions/xep-0301.html#element_w_wait_interval">Element &lt;w/&gt; =E2=
=80=93 Wait Interval</a> between other <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensio=
ns/xep-0301.html#action_elements">Action Elements</a>. Sender clients can t=
ransmit the length of pauses between key presses, and send multiple key pre=
sses in a single &lt;message/&gt; stanza. Recipient clients that process &l=
t;w/&gt; elements are able to display the sender's typing smoothly without =
sudden bursts of text. See <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.=
html#examples_of_key_press_intervals">Examples of Key Press Intervals</a>.<=
/p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">When key press intervals are preserved at high=
 precision, all subtleties of typing are preserved, including the 'mood' (c=
alm typing versus panicked or emphatic typing, etc.). Much as Voice over IP=
 (VoIP) allows accurate packet transmission of sound, this spec allows accu=
rate packet transmission of original typing look-and-feel. This enables the=
 real-time feel of typing over virtually any network connection, without re=
quiring frequent transmission intervals. Look and feel of typing is also pr=
eserved over variable latency connections including <span class=3D"ref" sty=
le=3D""><a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0206.html">XMPP Over BOS=
H (XEP-0206)</a></span>  [<a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.h=
tml#nt-idm45597907211568">19</a>], mobile phone, satellite and long interna=
tional connections with heavy packet-bursting tendencies.</p>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h4 id=3D"time_critical_and_low_latency_methods">=
7.1.3 Time Critical and Low Latency Methods<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D=
"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#time_critical_and_low_latency_me=
thods"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the document">=C2=B6</abbr></a>=
</h4>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">There are specialized situations such as live =
transcriptions and captioning (e.g., transcription service, closed captioni=
ng provider, captioned telephone, Communication Access Realtime Translation=
 (CART), relay services) that demand low latency transmission. Such systems=
 typically use voice recognition and/or stenotype machines, which output te=
xt in word or phrase bursts rather than a character at a time. It can be ac=
ceptable for senders with bursty output to immediately transmit word or phr=
ase bursts of text without buffering, as long as the average stanza rate is=
 not excessive. This eliminates any lag caused by the <a href=3D"https://xm=
pp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#transmission_interval">Transmission Interva=
l</a>. It is not necessary to transmit <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensio=
ns/xep-0301.html#element_w_wait_interval">Element &lt;w/&gt; =E2=80=93 Wait=
 Interval</a> for real-time transcription.</p>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h4 id=3D"lowbandwidth_and_lowprecision_text_smoo=
thing">7.1.4 Low-Bandwidth and Low-Precision Text Smoothing<a class=3D"anch=
or-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#lowbandwidth_and=
_lowprecision_text_smoothing"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the docu=
ment">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h4>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Some software platforms (e.g., JavaScript, BOS=
H, mobile devices) may have low-precision timers that impact <a href=3D"htt=
ps://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#transmission_interval">Transmission =
Interval</a> and/or <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#pr=
eserving_key_press_intervals">Preserving Key Press Intervals</a>. Clients c=
an optimize for bandwidth, performance and/or screen repaints by eliminatin=
g, merging, or ignoring <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.htm=
l#element_w_wait_interval">Element &lt;w/&gt; =E2=80=93 Wait Interval</a> s=
electively, especially those containing shorter intervals. In addition, it =
is acceptable for the transmission interval of &lt;rtt/&gt; to vary, either=
 intentionally for optimizations, or due to precision limitation, preferabl=
y within the range recommended by <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xe=
p-0301.html#transmission_interval">Transmission Interval</a>. Compression c=
an also be used to reduce bandwidth (e.g., TLS compression or <span class=
=3D"ref" style=3D""><a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0138.html">S=
tream Compression (XEP-0138)</a></span>  [<a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/exten=
sions/xep-0301.html#nt-idm45597907196336">20</a>]).</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Clients can choose to implement alternate text=
-smoothing methods, such as adaptive-rate character-at-a-time output, and/o=
r word buffering for incoming real-time text. Word buffering prevents most =
typing mistakes from being displayed, which can be a useful mode of operati=
on for certain recipients who may dislike watching the sender's typing mist=
akes.</p>
    </div>
</div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h3 id=3D"optional_remote_cursor">7.2 Optional Re=
mote Cursor<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep=
-0301.html#optional_remote_cursor"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the=
 document">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h3>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Recipient clients can choose to display a remo=
te cursor within incoming real-time messages. A remote cursor is a separate=
 cursor/caret indicator within incoming real-time messages, separate of the=
 user's local cursor for outgoing messages. This can improve usability of r=
eal-time text, since it becomes easier for a recipient to observe the sende=
r's real-time message edits. For clients that do not implement a remote cur=
sor, skip this section.</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D""><a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-030=
1.html#action_elements">Action Elements</a> use only absolute positioning (=
relative positions are not used by this specification), so clients do not n=
eed to remember the position value from previous action elements. Recipient=
 software can calculate the remote cursor position as follows:</p>
    <ul class=3D"" style=3D"">
      <li class=3D"" style=3D""><p class=3D"" style=3D"">Upon receiving <a =
href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#element_t_insert_text">El=
ement &lt;t/&gt; =E2=80=93 Insert Text</a>, the cursor position is the 'p' =
attribute plus the length of the text being inserted. The cursor position i=
s put at the end of the inserted text.<br>
        <em>This allows normal forward cursor movement during text insertio=
n.</em></p></li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D""><p class=3D"" style=3D"">Upon receiving <a =
href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#element_e_erase_text">Ele=
ment &lt;e/&gt; =E2=80=93 Erase Text</a>, the cursor position is the 'p' at=
tribute minus the 'n' attribute.<br>
        <em>This allows normal backwards cursor movement to a backspace key=
.</em></p></li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D""><p class=3D"" style=3D"">Upon receiving an =
empty <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#element_t_insert=
_text">Element &lt;t/&gt; =E2=80=93 Insert Text</a> (e.g., &lt;t p=3D'#'/&g=
t; or &lt;t p=3D'#'&gt;&lt;/t&gt;), the cursor position is the 'p' attribut=
e and no text modification is done. Senders can send these elements when on=
ly the cursor position has changed (e.g., arrow keys, mouse repositioning).=
 These are non-operative elements on recipients that do not implement a rem=
ote cursor.</p></li>
    </ul>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h3 id=3D"sending_realtime_text">7.3 Sending Real=
-Time Text<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-=
0301.html#sending_realtime_text"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the d=
ocument">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h3>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">This section lists several possible methods of=
 generating real-time text for transmission. For most situations, the prefe=
rred methodology is <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#mo=
nitoring_message_changes_instead_of_key_presses">Monitoring Message Changes=
 Instead Of Key Presses</a>.</p>
        <div class=3D"indent"><h4 id=3D"monitoring_message_changes_instead_=
of_key_presses">7.3.1 Monitoring Message Changes Instead Of Key Presses<a c=
lass=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#moni=
toring_message_changes_instead_of_key_presses"><abbr title=3D"Link to this =
point in the document">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h4>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Experience has found that the most reliable me=
thod for generating real-time text, is to monitor for <strong>text changes<=
/strong> to the sender=E2=80=99s message entry field, instead of key press =
events. Text change events have the following advantages:</p>
    <ul class=3D"" style=3D"">
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">It captures all typing, including edits and=
 deletes.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">It captures copy &amp; paste operations, as=
 well as edits made via a pointing device.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">It captures all automatic text changes (e.g=
., spell checker, auto-correct, macros, transcription, assistive devices).<=
/li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">It captures characters requiring multiple k=
ey presses to compose (e.g., accents, combining marks).</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">It makes no assumptions about different key=
boards or input method editors (e.g., Chinese).</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Text change events are more portable across=
 platforms, including on mobile phones.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">During a text change event, the sender=E2=80=
=99s current message text can be compared to the old message text from the =
previous text change event. The difference in text, between consecutive tex=
t change events, is typically a one character difference (e.g., key press) =
or one text block difference (e.g., auto-correct, cut, paste). In order to =
calculate what text changes took place, the first changed character and the=
 last changed character are determined. From this, it is simple to generate=
 <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#action_elements">Acti=
on Elements</a> for a single text block deletion and/or insertion. In addit=
ion, if <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#preserving_key=
_press_intervals">Preserving Key Press Intervals</a> is supported, then <a =
href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#element_w_wait_interval">=
Element &lt;w/&gt; =E2=80=93 Wait Interval</a> records the time elapsed bet=
ween text change events.</p>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Sender software can do the following:</p>
    <ol start=3D"" class=3D"" style=3D"">
      <li class=3D"" style=3D""><p class=3D"" style=3D"">Monitor for text c=
hanges in the sender=E2=80=99s message. Whenever a text change event occurs=
, compute action element(s) and append these action element(s) to a buffer.=
 Repeating this step during every text change event, is equivalent to recor=
ding a small sequence of typing.</p></li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D""><p class=3D"" style=3D"">During every <a hr=
ef=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#transmission_interval">Tran=
smission Interval</a>, all buffered action elements are transmitted in &lt;=
rtt/&gt; element in a &lt;message/&gt; stanza. This is equivalent to transm=
itting a small sequence of typing at a time.</p></li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D""><p class=3D"" style=3D"">If there are no me=
ssage changes occurring, no unnecessary transmission takes place.</p></li>
    </ol>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h4 id=3D"monitoring_key_presses_directly">7.3.2 =
Monitoring Key Presses Directly<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmp=
p.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#monitoring_key_presses_directly"><abbr title=
=3D"Link to this point in the document">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h4>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">Real-time text can be generated via monitoring=
 key presses. However, this does not have the advantages of <a href=3D"http=
s://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#monitoring_message_changes_instead_of=
_key_presses">Monitoring Message Changes Instead Of Key Presses</a>. Care n=
eeds be taken with automatic changes to the message, generated by means oth=
er than key presses. This includes spell check auto-correct, copy and paste=
s, transcription, input method editors, and multiple key presses required t=
o compose a character (i.e., accents). Key press events can miss these text=
 changes, and this can potentially cause incorrect real-time text to be tra=
nsmitted.</p>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h4 id=3D"appendonly_realtime_text">7.3.3 Append-=
Only Real-Time Text<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extens=
ions/xep-0301.html#appendonly_realtime_text"><abbr title=3D"Link to this po=
int in the document">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h4>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">The use of <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensi=
ons/xep-0301.html#element_t_insert_text">Element &lt;t/&gt; =E2=80=93 Inser=
t Text</a> without any attributes, simply appends text to the end of a mess=
age, while the use of <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#=
element_e_erase_text">Element &lt;e/&gt; =E2=80=93 Erase Text</a> without a=
ny attributes, simply erases text from the end of the message. This sending=
 method can also be useful for special-purpose clients where mid-message ed=
iting capabilities are not used (e.g., simple transcription, news tickers, =
relay services, captioned telephone).</p>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"indent"><h4 id=3D"simple_realtime_text">7.3.4 Simple Real=
-Time Text<a class=3D"anchor-link" href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-=
0301.html#simple_realtime_text"><abbr title=3D"Link to this point in the do=
cument">=C2=B6</abbr></a></h4>
    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">It is possible for sender clients to use <a hr=
ef=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#message_refresh">Message Re=
fresh</a> to simply re-transmit the whole real-time message, as a method of=
 transmitting text changes. The advantage is very simple implementation. Di=
sadvantages can include the lack of <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/=
xep-0301.html#preserving_key_press_intervals">Preserving Key Press Interval=
s</a>, and extra bandwidth consumption that can occur with longer messages,=
 unless stream compression is used. The below illustrates transmission of t=
he real-time message =E2=80=9C<strong>Hello there!</strong>=E2=80=9D at a r=
egular <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#transmission_in=
terval">Transmission Interval</a> while the sender is typing.</p>
    <figure class=3D"code"><figcaption></figcaption><pre class=3D"prettypri=
nt prettyprinted" style=3D""><span class=3D"tag">&lt;message</span><span cl=
ass=3D"pln"> </span><span class=3D"atn">to</span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</s=
