    <p class=3D"" style=3D"">This example also illustrates the following:</=
p>
    <ul class=3D"" style=3D"">
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Typing is done via <a href=3D"https://xmpp.=
org/extensions/xep-0301.html#element_t_insert_text">Element &lt;t/&gt; =E2=
=80=93 Insert Text</a>.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Backspaces are done via <a href=3D"https://=
xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#element_e_erase_text">Element &lt;e/&gt; =
=E2=80=93 Erase Text</a>.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">There is a final transmission with a <a hre=
f=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#body_element">Body Element</=
a>, when the message is finished.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Intervals between key presses are done via =
<a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#element_w_wait_interva=
l">Element &lt;w/&gt; =E2=80=93 Wait Interval</a>.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Each &lt;message/&gt; is delivered at a reg=
ular <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#transmission_inte=
rval">Transmission Interval</a>, typically 700 milliseconds.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Cursor movements via empty &lt;t/&gt; eleme=
nts. Sender transmission is not essential, but can be desirable for recipie=
nt clients supporting an <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.ht=
ml#optional_remote_cursor">Optional Remote Cursor</a>.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">Recipient clients that do not support <a hr=
ef=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#preserving_key_press_interv=
als">Preserving Key Press Intervals</a> and/or <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/=
extensions/xep-0301.html#optional_remote_cursor">Optional Remote Cursor</a>=
, will still display this message normally.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">The total sum of all values in <a href=3D"h=
ttps://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#element_w_wait_interval">Element &=
lt;w/&gt; =E2=80=93 Wait Interval</a> in one &lt;message/&gt; equal the <a =
href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#transmission_interval">Tr=
ansmission Interval</a> during periods of continuous typing. This also resu=
lts in some &lt;w/&gt; interval elements being split between consecutive me=
ssages. Although not critical, it can further improve the fluidity of <a hr=
ef=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0301.html#receiving_realtime_text">Re=
ceiving Real-Time Text</a>.</li>
      <li class=3D"" style=3D"">See <a href=3D"https://xmpp.org/extensions/=
xep-0301.html#monitoring_message_changes_instead_of_key_presses">Monitoring=
 Message Changes Instead Of Key Presses</a> for the best method of implemen=
tation.</li>
    </ul>
